{"lemma": "لِ", "slug": "لِ", "root": "NTWS", "root_slug": "NTWS", "root_link": "/words/roots/NTWS", "pos": "PREP", "pos_camel": "prep", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "لِ", "root": "", "pos": "P", "occurrence_count": 4380}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 8, "pos_tags": ["character", "conj", "particle", "prep", "symbol", "verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 10}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n37412", "n43184"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%84%D9%90"}}, "translations": {"en": "to, for", "fa": "برای، به", "ur": "کو، کے لیے", "tr": "için, için", "id": "kepada, untuk", "bn": "কে, জন্য", "es": "a, para", "fr": "à, pour", "de": "zu, für", "ru": "к, для", "zh": "给，为了"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "character", "gloss": "The twenty-third letter of the Arabic alphabet, written in the Arabic script; preceded by ك (k) and followed by م (m).", "tags": ["letter"]}, {"pos": "symbol", "gloss": "The twelfth numeral symbol of the Arabic alphabet (traditional abjad order, used for list numbering), written in the Arabic script; preceded by ك (k) and followed by م (m)."}, {"pos": "prep", "gloss": "to, for, belonging to", "examples": [{"text": "تَيَسَّرَ لِلسَّفَرِ", "english": "Travel became easy."}]}, {"pos": "prep", "gloss": "Used to express admiration", "examples": [{"text": "يَا لَلْعَجَبِ!", "english": "How wonderful!"}, {"text": "يَا لَهُ مِنْ عَالَمٍ رَائِعٍ!", "english": "What a wonderful world!"}]}, {"pos": "prep", "gloss": "Used to call for help", "examples": [{"text": "يَا لَلْأُمِّ لِلْأَطْفَالِ!", "english": "Oh for mother to the children! (Oh mother, help your children!)"}]}, {"pos": "conj", "gloss": "to, in order to: followed by the subjunctive mood", "examples": [{"text": "دَخَلْتُ ٱلْمَطْبَخَ لِأَشْرَبَ مَاءً.", "english": "I entered the kitchen to drink water."}]}, {"pos": "conj", "gloss": "used with the verbs أَرَادَ (ʔarāda) and أَمَرَ (ʔamara)", "examples": [{"text": "إِنَّمَا يُرِيدُ اللّٰهُ لِيُذْهِبَ عَنْكُمُ الرِّجْسَ", "english": "Allah only intends to purify you of impurity."}]}, {"pos": "conj", "gloss": "only to (لَامُ الْعَاقِبَة (lāmu l-ʕāqiba))", "examples": [{"text": "فَالْتَقَطَهُ آلُ فِرْعَوْنَ لِيَكُونَ لَهُمْ عَدُوًّا وَحَزَنًا", "english": "And so the family of the Pharaoh picked him up, only to become an enemy and a grief."}]}, {"pos": "particle", "gloss": "Used to introduce an imperative with a jussive verb; let", "examples": [{"text": "لِتَأْخُذُوا مَنَاسِكَكُمْ فَإِنِّي لَا أَدْرِي لَعَلِّي لَا أَحُجُّ بَعْدَ حَجَّتِي هَذِهِ", "english": "Learn your rituals from me, for I do not know—perhaps this will be my last Hajj."}, {"text": "وَقُلِ ٱلْحَقُّ مِنْ رَبِّكُمْ فَمَنْ شَاءَ فَلْيُؤْمِنْ وَمَنْ شَاءَ فَلْيَكْفُرْ", "english": "And say, \"The truth is from your Lord, so whoever wills, let him believe; and whoever wills, let him disbelieve.\""}]}, {"pos": "particle", "gloss": "truly, verily, certainly, surely", "examples": [{"text": "وَإِنَّ أَوْهَنَ ٱلْبُيُوتِ لَبَيْتُ ٱلْعَنْكَبُوتِ", "english": "And indeed, the weakest of homes is the home of the spider."}, {"text": "إِنَّ رَبَّكَ لَبِالْمِرْصَادِ", "english": "Verily, thy Lord is on the lookout."}]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "From the Nabataean Aramaic letter 𐢑 (l, “lāmaḏ”), derived from the Phoenician letter 𐤋 (l, “lāməd”), from the Egyptian hieroglyph 𓌅. See also Classical Syriac ܠ (l, “lāmaḏ”), Hebrew ל (l, “lamed”), Ancient Greek Λ (L), Greek Λ (L), Latin L.\n\nFrom Proto-Semitic *lV-."}, "ipa": ["/laːm/", "/l/", "/ɫ/", "/li./", "/la./"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n37412", "headword_ar": "ل", "root": "l", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The twenty-third letter of the alphabet;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laAmN", "text_ar": "لَامٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". It is one of the letters termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "majohuwrap", "text_ar": "مَجْهُورَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", or vocal, and also belongs to the class of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHuruwfu", "text_ar": "الحُرُوفُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al*~uloqu", "text_ar": "الذُّلْقُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*awolaqiy~ap", "text_ar": "ذَوْلَقِيَّة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e. letters pronounced by means of the tip of the tongue and the lip; it is one of the letters of augmentation.       -A2-  As a numeral it denotes"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "thirty."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "-A3-  For the particles"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lA li la", "text_ar": "لا لِ لَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", &c., see Supplement."}], "source_refs": []}, {"entry_id": "n43184", "headword_ar": "ل", "root": "l", "body": [{"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "l", "text_ar": "ل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "—"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lanaA fiY baniY fulaAnK dimaA='N", "text_ar": "لَنَا فِى بَنِى فُلَانٍ دِمَا=ءٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "We have a claim, upon the sons of such a one, to blood,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "lit."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bloods"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xbl", "text_ar": "خبل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lahu A^ano yafoEala ka*aA", "text_ar": "لَهُ اَنْ يَفْعَلَ كَذَا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He shall have a right to do such a thing:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaqaba", "text_ar": "عَقَبَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raA^ayotu lahu bariyqFA", "text_ar": "رَاَيْتُ لَهُ بَرِيقًا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I saw it to have a glistening:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "samiEotu lahu SawotFA", "text_ar": "سَمِعْتُ لَهُ صَوْتًا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I heard him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it, to have a sound"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "proceeding from him, or it; or rather,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I heard a sound attributable,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to be attributed, to him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I heard him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it, utter"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "produce, a sound;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I heard in consequence of it,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c. (see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saTaEN", "text_ar": "سَطَعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "). ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lahu ka*aA", "text_ar": "لَهُ كَذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "often means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a thing appertains,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "is attributable, to him,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "―         -b5-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA lanaA A^al~aA nuqaAtila", "text_ar": "مَا لَنَا اَلَّا نُقَاتِلَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the Kur ii. 247, [i. e."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ano laA", "text_ar": "اَنْ لَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",] means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "What object have we"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aY~u garaDK lanaA", "text_ar": "اَىُّ غَرَضٍ لَنَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY", "text_ar": "فِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that we should not fight?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in our"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "not fighting?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Bd:) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA lanaA A^al~aA natawak~ala EalaY", "text_ar": "مَا لَنَا اَلَّا نَتَوَكَّلَ عَلَى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A@ll~`hi", "text_ar": "ا@للّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the same, xiv. 15, means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "What excuse have we"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aY~u Eu*orK lanaA", "text_ar": "اَىُّ عُذْرٍ لَنَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY", "text_ar": "فِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that we should not rely upon God?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in our"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "not relying upon God?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Bd.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA lanaA A^ano laA nafoEala ka*aA", "text_ar": "مَا لَنَا اَنْ لَا نَفْعَلَ كَذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[may be rendered"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "What reason,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "motive, have we that we should not do such a thing?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in that,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.? or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in our not doing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.? for] the original form of the phrase is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA lanaA fiY A^ano laA nafoEala ka*aA", "text_ar": "مَا لَنَا فِى اَنْ لَا نَفْعَلَ كَذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mugh, voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ano", "text_ar": "اَنْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) Often"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^ano", "text_ar": "اَنْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is omitted, but meant to be understood: you say also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA laka", "text_ar": "مَا لَكَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tafoEalu ka*aA", "text_ar": "تَفْعَلُ كَذَا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "What reason,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "motive, hast thou"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "that"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "thou dost such a thing?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "what aileth thee"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.? It is often like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA baAluka", "text_ar": "مَا بَالُكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b6-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gar~ada biSawotK lahu", "text_ar": "غَرَّدَ بِصَوْتٍ لَهُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "DaEiyfK", "text_ar": "ضَعِيفٍ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(a bird)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "warbled with a feeble voice peculiar to it."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "―         -b7-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA liY walilobagi baEoDikumo EalaY baEoDi", "text_ar": "مَا لِى وَلِلْبَغِ بَعْضِكُمْ عَلَى بَعْضِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA liY A^araAka tafoEalu ka*aA bagaY", "text_ar": "مَا لِى اَرَاكَ تَفْعَلُ كَذَا بَغَى"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "What hath happened to me that I see thee doing such a thing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "thus?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "See an ex. in conj. 3 of art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "blw", "text_ar": "بلو"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b8-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA laka bika*aA", "text_ar": "مَا لَكَ بِكَذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see a verse cited in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Elw", "text_ar": "علو"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b9-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^anaA lahaA", "text_ar": "اَنَا لَهَا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I am for it;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e., I am the man for it; meaning a war, or battle,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HarobN", "text_ar": "حَرْبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is of the fem. gender. Often occurring in old Arabic stories. ―         -b10-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "li", "text_ar": "لِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the sense of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY", "text_ar": "فِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see Msb, voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eid~apN", "text_ar": "عِدَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b11-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mano liY", "text_ar": "مَنْ لِى"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Who is,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "will be, for me, as aider,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "helper,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "defender,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "surely?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "For exs., see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "saboEN", "text_ar": "سَبْعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$abara", "text_ar": "شَبَرَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^afovaA^a", "text_ar": "اَفْثَاَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". ―         -b12-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "taEosFA lahu", "text_ar": "تَعْسًا لَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "quboHaA lahu", "text_ar": "قُبْحَا لَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "natonFA lahu", "text_ar": "نَتْنًا لَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", &c.: see the first word of each of these phrases. ―         -b13-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mano liY bika*aA", "text_ar": "مَنْ لِى بِكَذَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bi", "text_ar": "بِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(near the end of the paragraph): and see also above. ―         -b14-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "te